The National Cohesion and Integration Commission on Wednesday warned that the hardline stances taken by political outfits over the IEBC appeal on presidential elections tallying is threatening the country's stability.The EBC has challenged the High Court decision that presidential election results announced at the constituency level will be final.On April 7, judges Aggrey Muchelule, Weldon Korir and Chacha Mwita ruled that returning officers at the constituency level will make the final decision on all election results, including the presidential votes.